text: Tamin (, also Romanized as Tamīn and Temīn; also known as Tamīn-e Pā’īn) is a village in Tamin Rural District, in the Central District of Mirjaveh County, Sistan and Baluchestan Province, Iran. At the 2006 census, its population was 457, in 81 families. == References == Category:Populated places in Mirjaveh County
title: Tamin
